{"text":{"description":[{"type":"text","value":"Gov. Greg Gianforte, elected in Nov. 2020, took office in early 2021 as Montana’s first Republican governor since 2005."},{"type":"text","value":"The governor appoints state agency heads and is ultimately responsible for the day-to-day management of government. The governor also prepares a budget proposal that serves as a starting point for the legislative appropriations process, where lawmakers determine how much the governor’s executive branch is allowed to spend."},{"type":"text","value":"Bills passed by the Legislature are sent to the governor, who can sign them into law, issue a veto, or let them become law without his signature. Vetos can be overridden by two-thirds majority votes in both the House and Senate."}]},"articles":[{"title":"Gianforte stresses ‘resilience’ in first State of the State address","subtitle":"","date":"2021-01-29T20:56:28.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/29/gianforte-stresses-resilience-in-first-state-of-the-state-address/","tags":["2021 Legislature","Greg Gianforte","State of the State"],"author":"Amanda Eggert","imageUrl":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/29/gianforte-stresses-resilience-in-first-state-of-the-state-address/state-of-the-state-21-29/","billTags":[],"lawmakerTags":[],"governorTags":["Greg Gianforte"]},{"title":"Raising teacher salaries","subtitle":"","date":"2021-01-26T20:00:01.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/26/raising-teacher-salaries/","tags":["2021 Legislature","Amanda Curtis","Briefs","Glenn Oppel","Greg Gianforte","House Bill 143","Llew Jones","MFPE","Montana Federation of Public Employees","quality educator payment"],"author":"Alex Sakariassen","imageUrl":null,"billTags":["HB 143"],"lawmakerTags":["Llew Jones"],"governorTags":["Greg Gianforte"]},{"title":"The Session podcast","subtitle":"","date":"2021-01-25T15:56:40.000Z","link":"https://montanafreepress.org/2021/01/25/the-session-podcast/","tags":["2021 Legislature","Danny Te